the practices in Milwaukee

91
00:04:01,467 --> 00:04:06,067
generate an overrepresentation
of Black people in prison

92
00:04:06,100 --> 00:04:07,967
so that it's the highest
in the nation.

93
00:04:08,967 --> 00:04:12,767
If you're a Black person,
Black resident in Wisconsin,

94
00:04:13,767 --> 00:04:15,167
you have a 12 times
higher chance

95
00:04:15,267 --> 00:04:19,433
of being incarcerated
than a white Wisconsinite.

96
00:04:19,533 --> 00:04:21,633
- Seymour: History tells us
the over-policing of Blacks

97
00:04:21,733 --> 00:04:23,467
in Wisconsin
and across the country

98
00:04:23,567 --> 00:04:26,100
dates back
to the end of slavery.

99
00:04:26,200 --> 00:04:28,267
- When the 13th Amendment
to the Constitution

100
00:04:28,367 --> 00:04:31,267
was ratified
in December of 1865,

101
00:04:31,367 --> 00:04:33,700
most people never read
what it says.

102
00:04:33,800 --> 00:04:36,967
- It abolishes slavery,
and then there's a semi-colon,

103
00:04:37,067 --> 00:04:38,467
"Except for punishment

104
00:04:38,567 --> 00:04:40,867
for those who have been
found guilty of a felony."

105
00:04:40,967 --> 00:04:45,533
- It creates the ability
for you to be back in slavery

106
00:04:45,633 --> 00:04:46,800
in a different form.

107
00:04:46,900 --> 00:04:48,067
Something like loitering,

108
00:04:48,167 --> 00:04:50,733
which had never been illegal
before, becomes illegal.

109
00:04:50,833 --> 00:04:52,200
- Whistling in public.

110
00:04:53,467 --> 00:04:56,333
Like, I mean,
like that level of nonsense.

111
00:04:56,433 --> 00:04:59,133
Walking along a railroad track,

112
00:04:59,233 --> 00:05:04,200
not being able to produce
employment papers on demand.

113
00:05:04,300 --> 00:05:06,733
You steal a pig,
you go to prison for life.

114
00:05:07,733 --> 00:05:09,067
- Instead of sending you
to prison,

115
00:05:09,167 --> 00:05:11,433
someone who owns a plantation
or a mine

116
00:05:11,533 --> 00:05:13,733
or some business
who wants some free labor,

117
00:05:13,833 --> 00:05:16,100
they'll be able to come in
and grab you

118
00:05:16,200 --> 00:05:17,933
and put you into that system

119
00:05:18,067 --> 00:05:19,533
so that you're
not gonna go to prison.

120
00:05:19,633 --> 00:05:21,700
Now you're gonna go back
and work for free.

121
00:05:21,800 --> 00:05:23,200
- Society says, "Oh, my gosh,

122
00:05:23,300 --> 00:05:26,967
Black people have a propensity
to commit crimes,"

123
00:05:27,067 --> 00:05:28,833
versus what was going on,

124
00:05:28,933 --> 00:05:31,767
which was they were
arresting Black people

125
00:05:31,867 --> 00:05:35,467
for committing no crime, and
then sending them to slavery.

126
00:05:36,967 --> 00:05:38,267
- Seymour: The small town
of Appleton

127
00:05:38,367 --> 00:05:40,767
was once the center of one
of the most racist tactics used

128
00:05:40,867 --> 00:05:44,167
across the country to keep
Blacks out of white communities.

129
00:05:45,700 --> 00:05:48,667
- Meyn: Appleton doesn't really
have any Black people,

130
00:05:48,767 --> 00:05:50,100
and if you asked people
in Appleton,

131
00:05:50,200 --> 00:05:52,667
it's just because Black people
didn't wanna move there.

132
00:05:52,767 --> 00:05:56,733
Black people lived in Appleton
before the 1880s,

133
00:05:56,833 --> 00:05:59,733
and they attempted to join
a growing community

134
00:05:59,833 --> 00:06:01,700
during the '40s and '50s,

135
00:06:01,800 --> 00:06:04,867
but it was a sundown town
through 1970

136
00:06:04,967 --> 00:06:06,433
and enforced by the police.

137
00:06:07,533 --> 00:06:08,700
- Seymour: Sundown towns
were places

138
00:06:08,800 --> 00:06:09,933
that didn't allow Blacks

139
00:06:10,067 --> 00:06:11,900
and other people of color
after dark.

140
00:06:12,900 --> 00:06:14,700
- Jackson: They were
all over Wisconsin.

141
00:06:14,800 --> 00:06:17,833
- Seymour: Nearly 250 in all,
according to a database

142
00:06:17,933 --> 00:06:21,167
