sociologist James Loewen.

143
00:06:22,500 --> 00:06:24,900
- Dr. Christy Clark-Pujara:
So, Black people
can be there as workers,

144
00:06:25,067 --> 00:06:27,267
they can come to fish
during the day,

145
00:06:27,367 --> 00:06:29,067
but you'd better
be out by night.

146
00:06:30,067 --> 00:06:32,700
- Jackson: Some places
had a horn that would ring

147
00:06:32,800 --> 00:06:35,300
in the evening when it was time
for Black people to get out.

148
00:06:35,400 --> 00:06:38,167
Some places literally had signs
on the side of the roadway

149
00:06:38,267 --> 00:06:40,167
that said, you know,
"After the sun sets,

150
00:06:40,267 --> 00:06:41,833
Black people,
you're not welcome here."

151
00:06:42,833 --> 00:06:43,900
- Seymour: About that time,

152
00:06:44,067 --> 00:06:45,533
the prison population
in Wisconsin

153
00:06:45,633 --> 00:06:48,667
and everywhere else
begins to explode.

154
00:06:48,767 --> 00:06:50,700
[dramatic trumpet music]

155
00:06:52,267 --> 00:06:53,600
- Reporter: Six days of rioting

156
00:06:53,700 --> 00:06:55,800
in a Negro section
of Los Angeles left...

157
00:06:55,900 --> 00:06:57,067
- Meyn: After the Watts riot,

158
00:06:57,100 --> 00:06:58,700
white people blamed Black people
for the problem.

159
