178
00:07:54,667 --> 00:07:55,967
- Officer 2:
Open the door, man.

179
00:07:56,067 --> 00:07:59,100
- Meyn: It was changing the face
of corrections and policing.

180
00:07:59,200 --> 00:08:00,800
- Officer 1: So if
you cooperate...

181
00:08:00,900 --> 00:08:03,867
- All of that money focused
on those communities of color.

182
00:08:03,967 --> 00:08:06,367
- You end up with
a disproportionate population

183
00:08:06,467 --> 00:08:08,500
that are under
the criminal justice system.

184
00:08:08,600 --> 00:08:12,767
- If you live in the quote,
unquote hood and poor areas,

185
00:08:12,867 --> 00:08:14,400
you are policed in a way

186
00:08:14,500 --> 00:08:17,633
that people in affluent areas
are not, right?

187
00:08:17,733 --> 00:08:20,300
And so you are just more likely
to find yourself

188
00:08:20,400 --> 00:08:22,200
in front of a judge.

189
00:08:23,267 --> 00:08:27,700
- White individuals,
their cases get dismissed

190
00:08:28,700 --> 00:08:31,733
at a rate 50% higher
than the Black individuals.

191
00:08:33,067 --> 00:08:34,900
There's a higher rate
of sentencing Black individuals

192
00:08:35,067 --> 00:08:38,967
