for those incarcerated.

207
00:09:09,067 --> 00:09:11,067
- The increased crime indicated

208
00:09:11,167 --> 00:09:13,733
that we needed more prisons
at the time,

209
00:09:13,833 --> 00:09:15,900
and which I accommodated.

210
00:09:16,067 --> 00:09:17,867
But every time I did this,

211
00:09:17,967 --> 00:09:21,467
I always tried to balance
on the other side.

212
00:09:21,567 --> 00:09:23,333
I was big on welfare reform.

213
00:09:23,433 --> 00:09:25,800
I was big
on workforce development.

214
00:09:25,900 --> 00:09:28,267
I was big
on expanding education.

215
00:09:29,967 --> 00:09:32,367
- Domineé Meek:
In February of 1992,

216
00:09:32,467 --> 00:09:33,533
I had been expelled...

217
00:09:33,633 --> 00:09:34,700
- Seymour: At age 15,

218
00:09:34,800 --> 00:09:35,900
Domineé Meek received
a life sentence

219
00:09:36,067 --> 00:09:38,067
for taking the life
of Warren Smith, Junior,

220
00:09:38,133 --> 00:09:39,433
an innocent bystander.

221
00:09:40,433 --> 00:09:42,500
Domineé believes he and other
Black and brown teens

222
00:09:42,600 --> 00:09:43,667
receive harsher sentences

223
00:09:43,767 --> 00:09:45,533
compared with whites
the same age,

224
00:09:45,633 --> 00:09:47,067
convicted of the same crime.

225
00:09:47,100 --> 00:09:48,400
- Domineé Meek:
When I was incarcerated,

226
00:09:48,500 --> 00:09:50,967
I only met one person
that was white

227
00:09:51,067 --> 00:09:53,867
that was sentenced as a juvenile
to life in prison.

228
00:09:54,867 --> 00:09:56,333
They took Black boys

229
00:09:59,333 --> 00:10:01,667
and said that
"Y'all are Black men."

230
00:10:07,800 --> 00:10:09,800
And they punished us like men.

231
00:10:11,967 --> 00:10:14,433
They don't do that
to white boys.

232
00:10:15,800 --> 00:10:16,967
Not in the numbers.

233
00:10:22,200 --> 00:10:23,367
They gave them help.

234
00:10:25,933 --> 00:10:28,367
- In Wisconsin,
the number of, kind of,

235
00:10:28,467 --> 00:10:31,033
criminal referrals
is three times higher

236
00:10:31,133 --> 00:10:32,933
for Black kids than white kids.

237
00:10:33,933 --> 00:10:36,067
- You got two or three
generations of Black parents

238
00:10:36,167 --> 00:10:37,567
who have been incarcerated.

239
00:10:37,667 --> 00:10:39,767
The majority of the people
locked up are Black and brown.

240
00:10:39,867 --> 00:10:42,433
So when you got
the majority of us locked up,

241
00:10:42,533 --> 00:10:44,900
you can't be a parent
from prison.

242
00:10:45,000 --> 00:10:46,367
So when that child
looks for that,

243
00:10:46,467 --> 00:10:49,100
only place he goes to get it
is in the streets.

244
00:10:49,200 --> 00:10:50,800
So we need father figures
to step up,

245
00:10:50,900 --> 00:10:54,233
somebody to be,
that I can call

246
00:10:54,333 --> 00:10:57,500
at 2 o'clock in the morning
and say,

247
00:10:57,600 --> 00:11:00,300
"Murv, I'm locked up,
can you come get me?"

248
00:11:00,400 --> 00:11:02,567
Or "Murv, I'm scared,
