the Civil Rights Movement,

695
00:30:00,967 --> 00:30:03,433
like the institution of slavery,

696
00:30:03,533 --> 00:30:08,000
as something that is uniquely
Southern, and it was not.

697
00:30:08,100 --> 00:30:09,533
- Seymour:
While the US Supreme Court's

698
00:30:09,633 --> 00:30:11,600
 <i>Brown versus</i>
 <i>the Board of Education</i> ruling

699
00:30:11,700 --> 00:30:12,933
in the late 1950s

700
00:30:13,033 --> 00:30:15,333
ordered all US schools
to desegregate,

701
00:30:15,433 --> 00:30:17,233
Milwaukee and other parts
of the state,

702
00:30:17,333 --> 00:30:21,267
like much of the nation,
didn't do so for decades.

703
00:30:21,367 --> 00:30:25,667
- The schools in Milwaukee
are not in line

704
00:30:25,767 --> 00:30:29,700
with <i>Brown versus the Board</i>
 <i>of Education</i> until 1979.

705
00:30:29,800 --> 00:30:32,567
- Reggie Jackson:
The city of Milwaukee's
public school system decided,

706
00:30:32,667 --> 00:30:34,367
"Well, we're gonna
build new schools,

707
00:30:34,467 --> 00:30:36,467
but we're gonna build them
on the south side,

708
00:30:36,567 --> 00:30:39,000
which is primarily
the white part of town, right?"

